.th PACK VII "June 1979"
.sh NAME
pack \*- pack the contents of a picture row
.sh SYNOPSIS
int
.bd pack
(buffer,numpix,pixwd)
.s3
int buffer[depth][rlenth]
.br
int numpix
.br
int pixwd
.s3
int depth
.br
int rlenth
.sh DESCRIPTION
.lp +9 9
buffer	input buffer as supplied to
.it setupb
or
.it setupr
.lp +9 9
numpix	number of pixels in
.it buffer
.lp +9 9
pixwd	number of pixels to pack per word
.s3
.lp +9 9
depth	maximum number of rows kept in
.it buffer
.lp +9 9
rlenth	maximum number of columns kept in
.it buffer
.i0
.s3
.it Pack
will pack a picture row.
A picture's density is determined from the picture's byte size, where
2^(SIZE-1) is the number of bits per pixel where SIZE is the picture
byte size.
If
.it pixwd
is 0 or 1, no packing is done and control returns immediately.
Otherwise, the contents of
.it buffer
are packed by shifting the pixels to the right side of
.it buffer
so that there are
.it pixwd
pixels in each word of
.it buffer.
.s3
Function value is -1 on error and +1 on success.
